Sure, the chances of it coming in with an inclination of 90° are the
same as it coming in on the ecliptic. In fact, neither is likely. Any
object coming into our Solar System will have an arbitrary inclination
(possible weighted by the shape of the galaxy). But the inclination
doesn't change the fact that a three solar mass object (and it could be
much more) passing anywhere near our Solar System is going to do Bad
Things.

