A stellar black hole has a mass, say 3-16 solar masses for arguments
sake. The gravitational force of a black hole at distance is no
different than any other mass (such as a star). Interactions (other
that head on collisions) follow Keplerian orbits just like stars,
planets, comets and other bodies.

A small black hole (with event horizon diameter of 25 mm) would
have a mass of about .84 x 10^25 kg or 1.4 earth masses.
