Although never say never this scenario seems extremely unlikely and
would require an unusually fast spinning BH with a very specific
Goldilocks style magnetic field for it to work at all. AFAIK we don't
have a particularly good handle on how strong the magnetic field of a
few solar mass BH is likely to be. neutron stars have pretty extreme
ones though at around 10^10 Gauss or so. A solar mass BH being more
compact still might be even stronger still.

