For a maximally spinning Kerr metric BH the innermost stable circular
orbit is at the event horizon (if going in the same sense as the spin
of the BH), but for a retrograde orbit it is at 9Rs. The inner region
is going to be pretty hairy but for regions well away from the strong
GR and magnetic influence it is just a gravitating mass.

